# Back to the Future

Fair point, I should’ve been explicit. The DeLorean is from the film Back to the Future (and its sequels), a Hollywood sci-fi comedy classic. It’s a time-travelling car, a modified DMC-12 with a shiny stainless-steel body, wedge-shaped design, and those iconic gull-wing doors that make it look like it’s ready to fly—even before it actually does. Its polished exterior hides a gloriously chaotic interior: a mess of 1980s dials, switches, and wires, with the glowing flux capacitor stealing the show as the gizmo that makes time travel possible at 88 mph, leaving blazing trails behind.

It’s a finicky beast, as much a character as the humans, with a knack for breaking down at the worst moments—like stranding you in 1955 with a dead battery. Despite its sleek looks, it’s got a scrappy underdog charm, always pulling through when it counts. It’s not just a car; it’s a rebellious, time-hopping icon that’s equal parts style, madness, and heart.